\newlabel{fig:convergence_rate}{{3}{1}{Figure: Absolute error \(|f(x_k)-f(x^\ast )|\) vs iteration (log scale). Colours follow agency categories. Horizontal dashed line: \(\varepsilon = 10^{-8}\) from \protect \texttt {experiment.convergence\_tolerance}, aligned with the plot generated by \protect \texttt {generate\_convergence\_rate\_plot()}. Divergent \(\alpha \) curves turn upward once numerical blow-up dominates}{fig:convergence_rate}{}}
